      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACKS ULTIMATE FURY NZ (10) resumes form a spell of seven months but was very good against the best of his age group last season, highlighted by a Gold Chalice win and Group 1 placing in the Rising Sun. Generally comes to hand very quickly, with three wins from five first-up appearances. Flies here, winning eight of 10 attempts and he was readied with two nice trials so expecting a bright start to the campaign. VIN NUMBER (2) came from this barrier last start and was beaten only 2m into fourth at this circuit and distance after leading and boxing on. Can give a sight again. DIAMOND ECLIPSE (11) has a decent record here. Hasn't raced since he finished second at Melton in December but has been readied with two trials, winning the latest. KIMCANDO (8) draws wide but is going well, coming off placings in the Canberra and Coolamon Cups having also won a Riverina Championships heat here in March.",
